As a customer, I'd like to have the option to have a different banner image for each portal (project). Currently, the banner set is applied to all the help center.

When:
 # adding a webhook with "comment added" trigger,
 # using a variable ${comment} on a custom payload, like: 
 \{{{ "message": "日本語のキーボード", "variable": "${comment}" }}}
 # I add a comment with the following text: \{ "message": "日本語のキーボード", "variable": "日本語のキーボード" }

Then: 
 # A webhook is called with an invalid payload, like this:

{ "message": "日本語のキーボード", "variable": "\\{ "message": "日本語のキーボード", "variable": "h1. 日本語のキーボード  " }

"
 }

h4. Problem

Whenever creating a request, retrieving "My Requests" list, or retrieving a single request, the following warning may be observed in the logs:
{noformat}
[c.a.s.i.f.customer.request.CustomerRequestInternalManagerImpl] The first customer request status found, does not appear to match the actual issues current customer request status. Attempt a re-sort operation before return results
{noformat}
This appears to occur when the status change for the issue contains multiple events happening in short order (like multiple automation rules being executed quickly). This seems to result in a jumbled activity list, leading JSD to perform an in-memory reordering for the list. However, the resulting (reordered) activity list _is not stored_ in the database, so the activity list needs to be re-sorted every time we retrieve the given issue. This re-sorting incurs some overhead each time and spams the logs with the above error.
h4. Workaround

The excessive logging can be suppressed by lowering the log level to *INFO* for this specific class:
{noformat}
com.atlassian.servicedesk.internal.feature.customer.request.CustomerRequestInternalManagerImpl
{noformat}
